channel.title: Player rights help
channel.description: When I go in my name file and change the player rights from 0(normal player) to 3(owner), save it, and compile it, it doesn't work. I can't see the crown although another guide said you can't see it in basic sources like testscape which is what im using, but I can't do anything like ::pnpc or ::npc or ::pickup. Is there a reason for this?

item.title: Player rights help
item.dc:creator: @k0_twin k0 twin
item.description:
@k0_twin wrote:

hybrent:

OK but i was really wondering how to edit mine because i don’t have a command that maxes. would I just do the same thing, but edit mine without logging?

you would do the same, but you DO need to log out when you save the changes. so first you would go into your character files, find your name, open it, scroll down untill you get to the player skills, and edit the first 6 or 7 (which are the combat) or just edit all of them. you need to change the experience (to around 14m) and the level to 99 (or whatever your max stat is. then log out, and save the changes, and simply log back in.

hybrent:

k0 is there a way to max someone because when i change it it just changes back when i log in. I have tried compiling it and not compiling it. Like is there anything in cline.java?

if your trying to max a non admins stats, because they cant do ::master of whatever it is for you, you said, “when i log back in it isnt working” and thats because YOU dont need to log out when editing somebodys skills or bank, THEY have to log out, so just kick them or ask them to log out for a few seconds, save changes, and your done, and youve succesfully edited there stats.
